# Revenue Reconciliation System

## Stack

- **API:** Laravel 12 (`backend/`), PHP 8.3, MySQL 8
- **UI:** Vue 3 (`packages/web/`), built into Laravel `public/` for production
- **Locations feed:** Each persisted location submits via HTTP (`LocationsFeedApiClient`, `x-source: LOC-xxx`); no in-process import bypass
- **Deploy:** Single Docker image `backend/Dockerfile`; production at [https://luckylincoln.xyz/](https://luckylincoln.xyz/) on Railway (see `deploy/railway/DEPLOY.md`)

## Local Docker

```bash
./start.sh   # http://localhost:18430
docker compose down -v   # full reset
```

Services: `mysql`, `app` (API + Vue + `schedule:work` + bootstrap locations-feed).

## Architecture

1. **Seed** (`reference_data.sql` in migration) — locations, machines, game_types, expected_totals; **no** revenue/submissions
2. **Locations feed** (`locations-feed:run`) — loads locations from API, POSTs per location to `/api/revenue/import`
3. **Import** — envelope for `LOC-*` sources; canonical `location_daily_files`; audit `import_batches`
4. **Schedule** — daily 00:00 UTC + resubmit every 15m (`routes/console.php`); bootstrap `--daily` on container start

## Key paths

| Area | Path |
|------|------|
| Import / idempotency | `backend/app/Services/ImportService.php` |
| Location source gate | `backend/app/Support/LocationSource.php` |
| Locations feed | `backend/app/Console/Commands/LocationsFeedCommand.php`, `backend/app/Services/LocationsFeedApiClient.php` |
| Config | `backend/config/locations-feed.php` |
| Diagrams | `backend/app/Services/DiagramService.php` |
| Entrypoint | `backend/docker/entrypoint.sh` |
| API routes | `backend/routes/api.php` |
| Vue UI | `packages/web/` |

## Env

- Docker: `LOCATIONS_FEED_DAILY_STAGGER_MS`, `LOCATIONS_FEED_INVALID_RESUBMIT_RATE`, `SEED_RANDOM`
- Docker DB: `DB_HOST=mysql`, `DB_DATABASE=revenue_db`
- Railway: MySQL → Connect app; app vars in `deploy/railway/DEPLOY.md` (no `FEEDER_*`, no manual `PORT`)
- Vue dev proxy: `VITE_API_PROXY=http://localhost:18430` when API runs in Docker

## Do not

- Reintroduce Node.js backend workers or `feeder:*` naming
- Seed revenue records or import via `ImportService` from the seeder/locations-feed command (HTTP only)
- Commit `backend/.env` (excluded from Docker via `.dockerignore`)
